        <section class="clearfix">
            <h2>Advancing Anatomy Education at the VR Lab | Metropolitan College Thessaloniki</h2>
            <p><em>Posted on December 03, 2024</em></p>

            <!-- Image container for vertical alignment -->
            <div class="image-container">
                <img src="fitness_fuel_1.png" alt="fitness_fuel1" class="enlargeable">
            </div>

            <p>Today, we took another significant step forward in the Anatomy VR Lab at Metropolitan College Thessaloniki, as our simulations officially commenced for this academic year. While our journey with virtual reality in anatomy education began last year, this marks the first time we've fully integrated the technology into our regular learning sessions.</p>
            <p>The lab classes continues to provide an interactive, detailed exploration of human anatomy, helping students visualize and understand complex systems with greater clarity. It's not just about innovation but about ensuring our teaching methods align with the needs of modern education.

        
            <!-- Vimeo video embed -->
            <div style="padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;"><iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1035671165?h=c3eeefd137" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;" title="Fitness_Fuel"></iframe></div><script src="https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js"></script>
        </section>

        <!-- The Modal -->
        <div id="myModal" class="modal">
            <span class="close">&times;</span>
            <div class="modal-content">
                <img id="imgModal">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Get modal element and the image inside it
        var modal = document.getElementById("myModal");
        var modalImg = document.getElementById("imgModal");
        var closeBtn = document.getElementsByClassName("close")[0];

        // Add event listeners to all images with class 'enlargeable'
        var images = document.getElementsByClassName("enlargeable");
        for (var i = 0; i < images.length; i++) {
            images[i].onclick = function() {
                modal.style.display = "block";
                modalImg.src = this.src;
            }
        }

        // When the user clicks on the close button, close the modal
        closeBtn.onclick = function() {
            modal.style.display = "none";
        }

        // When the user clicks anywhere outside the modal, close it
        window.onclick = function(event) {
            if (event.target == modal) {
                modal.style.display = "none";
            }
        }
    </script>
